[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    10[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    11[0m:[38;5;10m[49m This is the sixth recipe in Chapter 11 (Conversational AI / Virtual Assistants) and the chapter's first recipe to combine grounded clinical-protocol RAG, deterministic clinical-decision-rule computation as a tool, continuous-emergency-screening as a separately-validated pipeline, conservative-bias-by-default policy enforced architecturally, and FDA-strategy-alignment artifact as a versioned governance asset. It establishes the chapter's clinical-acuity-acute discipline (clinical-protocol corpus governance with medical-director sign-off as launch gate, conservative-bias-default as documented and audited policy, continuous-emergency-screening on every patient utterance not just first, clinical-decision-rule computation as deterministic tool with version stamping, citation-grounding as architectural floor with launch-gate threshold, nurse-line escalation as first-class capability with full conversation-context handoff, per-cohort over-triage and under-triage monitoring with separate thresholds, outcome-correlation pipeline as long-term operational commitment, FDA SaMD-strategy artifact maintenance, mandatory-reporting routing for sensitive disclosures, pediatric-and-adult protocol variants with special-population overlays, multilingual deployment with validated translations) and frames the chapter's posture toward patient-facing triage tools as patient-safety-acute clinical software that happens to use conversational AI rather than as conversational AI products that happen to retrieve triage protocols.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    12[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    13[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The opening Devon-with-the-2:14-AM-chest-pressure vignette earns its position as the chapter's strongest single articulation of the patient-decision-making-under-ambiguous-acute-symptom-uncertainty failure mode. The eleven-minute hold time on the nurse line, the four-minute structured-triage interview leading to "call 911," the ambulance arrival in fifteen minutes, the cath-lab placement at 4:47 AM, and the discharge on Thursday afternoon are operationally accurate and recipe-distinct. The "now scale that to every patient with an ambiguous symptom every night across the country" pivot into the high-acuity-patients-who-guess-wrong-miss-the-treatment-window framing is the recipe's strongest single passage on the misallocation-as-distributed-cost primitive. The "the questions Devon's nurse asked at 2:30 AM are not a mystery" pivot into the protocols-encode-decades-of-clinical-experience framing is the recipe's strongest single passage on the patient-cannot-navigate-the-decision-tree-alone primitive.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    14[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    15[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The Technology section is the chapter's introductory pedagogy on protocol-grounded conversational triage with conservative-by-default decision logic and executes at the right grain. The "Why Symptom-Triage Has Stayed Phone-Centric (And Why Most Web Symptom Checkers Failed)" subsection grounds the static-decision-tree-and-differential-generator failure modes in specific architectural diagnoses, with the references to Semigran et al. 2015, Hill et al. 2020, Ceney et al. 2021, Babylon Health, Buoy Health, Ada, K Health, Mayo Clinic, and Isabel Healthcare appropriately TODO-hedged. The "What a Triage Bot Actually Does" subsection's eight-stage decomposition (greeting and disclosure, crisis-and-emergency screening up front, symptom identification and protocol selection, structured protocol-driven questioning, acuity scoring and recommendation, recommendation delivery with disclaimers and instructions, nurse-line escalation, cross-channel continuity, audit and follow-up) is correctly granular and recipe-distinct. The "Why a Generic LLM Cannot Run a Triage Bot" subsection's nine-property enumeration is recipe-distinct and earns its position. The "What the Triage Bot Has To Do That the Previous Bots Did Not" subsection's six-structural-commitments enumeration (validated clinical-protocol corpus with medical-director sign-off, conservative-by-default acuity logic, continuous emergency-screening across every turn, clinical-decision-rule computation as deterministic tool, nurse-line escalation as architectural primitive, FDA-strategy alignment from day one) is the recipe's clearest articulation of the triage-bot-vs-other-chapter-11-bots-distinction primitive. The "Triage Reality" subsection's twelve-property enumeration is the recipe's most-distinctive contribution.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    16[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    17[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The ten-stage architecture (channel entry, input safety screening with continuous-emergency-screening, identity-and-chart-context loading, symptom identification and protocol selection, structured protocol-driven questioning, clinical-decision-rule computation, acuity scoring and recommendation, output safety screening with conservative-bias verification, recommendation delivery, nurse-line escalation when applicable) is the right shape and recipe-distinct from 11.5's nine-stage decomposition. The four new architectural primitives (clinical-protocol-corpus governance with medical-director sign-off, conservative-bias-default policy, continuous-emergency-screening pipeline, FDA-strategy-alignment artifact maintenance) are correctly elevated. The recipe-distinct cross-cutting design points (clinical-protocol corpus governance with effective-date and protocol-version metadata, conservative-bias-default policy as documented commitment, continuous-emergency-screening pipeline with held-out-emergency-case-corpus validation, citation-discipline as architectural primitive, clinical-decision-rule-computation as deterministic tool, nurse-line escalation as first-class capability, per-cohort monitoring as non-negotiable, conversation log as dense PHI plus may include sensitive disclosures, resumability across channels, disaster-recovery topology, outcome-correlation pipeline as long-term commitment) are correctly elevated.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    18[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    19[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The Why-These-Services section walks each AWS component back to the conceptual primitive it implements. The Honest Take is exceptionally strong, with ten traps earning the recipe's voice: institutional-content-as-someone-else's-problem recast as clinical-protocol-corpus-and-clinical-decision-rule-library-and-emergency-screening-corpus-and-regulatory-strategy-artifact-and-chart-context-integration-as-someone-else's-problem with multi-quarter-formalization-as-pre-deployment-investment; underestimating-conservative-bias-discipline with the every-architectural-decision-with-conservative-bias-as-explicit-policy framing; the regulatory-positioning trap with the FDA-experienced-regulatory-counsel-from-architectural-design framing; the citation-grounding-discipline trap with the bot-that-produces-ungrounded-recommendations-is-worse-than-no-triage-bot framing; the continuous-emergency-screening trap with the patient-who-three-turns-in-discloses-cauda-equina framing; shipping-without-nurse-line-integration; shipping-without-per-cohort-monitoring; shipping-without-outcome-correlation; shipping-without-explicit-equity-commitment; mishandling-sensitive-disclosures. The "thing that surprises engineers" / "thing that surprises clinical leaders" cross-discipline-comparisons earn their positions. The closing "the triage bot is the recipe in this chapter where the operational, clinical, and regulatory engineering most clearly outweighs the ML engineering" framing is the recipe's strongest single closing primitive, and the "start with a narrower set of protocols (the highest-volume routine presentations) before expanding to the high-stakes protocols" actionable takeaway earns its position as the chapter's analog of the self-deprecating-expertise-with-actionable-takeaway register.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    20[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    21[0m:[38;5;10m[49m That said, three correctness-and-compliance gaps at HIGH severity need attention before publication, plus one healthcare-domain accuracy issue at MEDIUM, plus the chapter-pattern set of MEDIUM and LOW items. The recipe contains explicit `<!-- TODO (TechWriter): Promote ... to architectural primitive -->` markers that anticipate the expert-review findings; the editor's job is to reconcile these against the actual findings and consolidate them in the next pass.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    22[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    23[0m:[38;5;10m[49m (1) **Clinical-protocol-corpus-as-code lifecycle and clinical-decision-rule-library and emergency-screening-corpus and FDA-strategy-artifact governance scaffolding underspecified despite explicit prose elevation.** The recipe correctly elevates clinical-protocol-corpus-as-versioned-governance-artifact-with-medical-director-signature-as-launch-gate, clinical-decision-rule-library-as-deterministic-code-with-formal-validation, emergency-screening-corpus-as-separately-validated-pipeline-with-false-negative-rate-as-launch-gate, and FDA-strategy-artifact-as-regulatory-counsel-reviewed-versioned-asset in five separate places. Despite this prose elevation, the architecture pattern, the diagram, and the pseudocode treat the corpus-and-library-and-corpus-and-artifact governance as institutional-policy reference rather than as architectural primitives with explicit version-control discipline, sandbox testing, staged rollout, named ownership, per-asset-version stamping on every triage-decision-record, and per-jurisdiction regulatory configuration. Recipe-acute amplification because the bot's clinical safety floor is bounded above by all four artifacts simultaneously and because the bot is the chapter's first recipe that approaches the FDA SaMD line with active regulatory exposure.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    24[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    25[0m:[38;5;10m[49m (2) **Triage-decision-record journal and tool-call ledger accumulate per-conversation content with potentially-PHI-rich free-text outside archive-reference pattern, with recipe-distinct PHI-and-mandatory-reporting-disclosure-as-additionally-sensitive and state-medical-records-retention-floor (especially pediatric retention until age-of-majority-plus-state-adult-retention-period) and FDA-SaMD-post-market-obligations amplifications.** Same chapter pattern as 11.4 and 11.5 with recipe-distinct extensions. The Step 8 persist_triage_decision_record write includes the full presenting_complaint, full protocol_answer_set, full clinical_rule_results, full recommendation_text, full active-version stamps. The Step 4 audit_tool_call writes for chart_context_lookup, intent_classify, emergency_screen, protocol_select, protocol_retrieve, clinical_rule_compute, recommendation_compose include the full retrieved member-specific data and full structured tool results. The recipe-distinct dimensions include the triage-decision-record-journal's combined-PHI-and-mandatory-reporting-and-FDA-SaMD-post-market retention floor (state medical records retention rules extend retention beyond HIPAA's six-year minimum in many states, particularly for adult records, with pediatric records often retained until age of majority plus the state's adult retention period; FDA SaMD post-market obligations may extend retention further), the per-record-class access-control surface, and the cross-correlation discipline with the institution's encounter-system-of-record and FHIR Encounter records. The recipe contains an explicit `<!-- TODO (TechWriter): Specify the working-store-vs-archive-store discipline -->` marker anticipating this finding.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    26[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    27[0m:[38;5;10m[49m (3) **Per-cohort over-triage-and-under-triage-and-citation-coverage-and-conservative-bias-compliance monitoring with launch-gate discipline architecturally implicit despite recipe's own elevation as central trap, with recipe-distinct over-triage-and-under-triage-as-separate-thresholds and per-emergency-category-sensitivity and outcome-correlation-accuracy and equity-disparity extensions.** Same chapter pattern as 11.1-11.5 Finding A1 with recipe-distinct triage extensions. The recipe correctly elevates per-cohort monitoring in five separate places (Cross-Cutting Design Points, Production-Gaps, Honest Take's seventh trap, Where-it-Struggles, Where-the-Field-Has-Moved equity discussion). Despite this thorough prose elevation, the architecture pattern, the diagram, and the pseudocode (Step 9 cloudwatch.put_metric calls) do not specify per-cohort launch-gate threshold values, two-axis and three-axis cohort stratification, per-cohort over-triage and under-triage rates as recipe-distinct separate-threshold metrics ("Aggregate accuracy is not a sufficient metric"), per-cohort outcome-correlation accuracy versus subsequent care utilization, per-cohort emergency-screening sensitivity per emergency category, per-cohort conservative-bias-compliance rate, per-cohort citation-coverage rate, per-cohort time-to-recommendation by acuity, per-cohort regulatory-disclaimer-presence rate, per-cohort equity-disparity flags, per-cohort sustained-utilization rate. Recipe-acute amplification because the bot is the chapter's first patient-safety-acute clinical recipe and the operational savings the recipe sells (avoided sit-at-home-with-MI cases, avoided ED-overload cases) are bounded above by the per-cohort over-triage and under-triage profile and the per-cohort emergency-screening sensitivity profile. The recipe contains explicit `<!-- TODO (TechWriter): Promote per-cohort monitoring to architectural primitive -->` and `<!-- TODO (TechWriter): Specify continuous-emergency-screening as a separately-validated pipeline -->` and `<!-- TODO (TechWriter): Promote outcome-correlation pipeline to architectural primitive -->` markers anticipating this finding.
