[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    137[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   1. **The triage-decision-record-journal is the recipe's load-bearing clinically-significant-record artifact.** Object Lock in compliance mode for the audit-pipeline retention window aligns with the audit pipeline retention; the triage-decision-record-journal also has state medical-records retention obligations that may be longer than the audit-pipeline retention floor (per-state medical-record retention rules vary; many states require 7-10+ years for adult records, with pediatric records often retained until age of majority plus the state's adult retention period, sometimes resulting in 25+ years of effective retention for triage decisions captured in pediatric encounters). FDA SaMD post-market obligations may extend retention further. The architecture should specify the per-state and per-pediatric and per-FDA-SaMD retention floor reconciliation and the per-record-class retention regime distinct from the audit-archive.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    138[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    139[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   2. **The decision_record's presenting_complaint, protocol_answer_set, clinical_rule_results, recommendation_text, and recommendation_rationale are clinically-significant elements with their own retention and access-control profiles.** The presenting_complaint contains the patient's free-text symptom description; the protocol_answer_set contains the structured answers to clinical-protocol questions including potentially-sensitive disclosures (mental-health crisis disclosures, intimate-partner violence disclosures, substance-use disclosures); the clinical_rule_results contains scores and risk strata that are part of the clinical record; the recommendation_text and recommendation_rationale contain the bot's reasoning as it appeared to the patient. Some elements are part of the formal medical record at some institutions; some are part of the audit-pipeline-by-others; each element has its own retention and access-control profile.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    140[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    141[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   3. **Mandatory-reporting-relevant disclosures are recipe-distinct additionally-sensitive content.** A patient's disclosure of child abuse, elder abuse, intimate-partner violence (in some states), or certain mental-health crisis types is statutorily protected with additional layers of access control, special handling, and per-jurisdiction reporting workflows. The architecture should specify the per-disclosure-class handling (sensitive disclosures route to a separately-governed sensitive-disclosure surface with restricted access; the triage-decision-record-journal should not embed mandatory-reporting-relevant disclosures inline without an explicit access-control gate).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    142[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    143[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   4. **The clinical-decision-rule arithmetic detail is part of the clinically-significant audit trail.** The HEART score, the Wells score, the Centor score, the Ottawa rules, and other rule scores have per-component breakdowns that are part of the reproducibility surface for the recommendation. The recipe's prose elevates "every clinical-rule score must trace to a tool result" (good); the architecture should specify the per-component breakdown is preserved with the rule result and made available through the citation surface for audit reproducibility.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    144[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    145[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   5. **The conversation log is dense PHI plus may include sensitive disclosures.** The recipe's prose correctly elevates this. The architecture should specify the per-record-class retention reconciliation (audit-archive retention vs triage-decision-record-journal retention vs conversation-log retention vs version-stamp-registry retention vs outcome-correlation-pending retention may differ; some institutions treat the conversation log as part of the medical record while others treat it as an audit-pipeline artifact; some state medical-record laws specifically address patient-communication retention).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    146[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    147[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   6. **The per-record-class access-control surface is not specified.** The audit pipeline's access-control surface is the audit-and-compliance team plus the privacy officer. The triage-decision-record-journal's access-control surface is the medical director plus the nurse-line operations team plus the compliance team plus the audit-and-compliance team plus the data-science team for outcome-correlation plus the patient (through the institution's patient-record-access pathway). The version-stamp-registry's access-control surface is the engineering team plus the audit-and-compliance team for incident review. The tool-call-ledger's access-control surface is the engineering team plus the audit-and-compliance team for incident review. The outcome-correlation-pending table's access-control surface is the data-science team plus the medical director. Each record class has different access-control needs.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    148[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    149[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   7. **The cross-correlation with the institution's encounter-system-of-record and FHIR Encounter records is recipe-distinct.** The outcome-correlation pipeline reads from the institution's encounter records (ED visits, urgent care visits, primary care visits, hospital admissions) and ideally from claims data for cross-institution utilization; the institution's encounter-system retention obligations apply alongside the triage-decision-record-journal's retention. The architecture should specify the cross-system reconciliation discipline and the data-flow from outcome-correlation-pending back to the triage-decision-record-journal with status updates.
