[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    176[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   1. **A successful prompt-injection on a triage-tool-LLM produces patient-safety consequences.** A malicious utterance that triggers the emergency_screen tool to suppress an emergency alert (a successful injection that causes the screen to return emergency_detected=False when the actual presentation is a true emergency), or a successful injection on the protocol_select tool that routes a chest-pain presentation to a low-acuity protocol, or a successful injection on the clinical_rule_compute tool that manipulates the HEART score inputs to lower the score, or a successful injection on the recommendation_compose tool that downgrades the care-level recommendation, all produce triage-decision-quality issues that propagate into the triage-decision-record-journal as durable incorrect-answer records and may cause direct patient harm.
